# @param {Integer[]} nums1
# @param {Integer[]} nums2
# @return {Integer}
def min_operations(nums1, nums2)
  operations = 0
  n = nums1.length
  max_num1 = nums1.max
  max_num2 = nums2.max

  # Swap if max value is not at the last position in either array
  if max_num1 != nums1[n - 1] || max_num2 != nums2[n - 1]
    if nums1[n - 1] != max_num1 && nums2.index(max_num1)
      nums1[n - 1], nums2[nums2.index(max_num1)] = nums2[nums2.index(max_num1)], nums1[n - 1]
      operations += 1
    end
    if nums2[n - 1] != max_num2 && nums1.index(max_num2)
      nums2[n - 1], nums1[nums1.index(max_num2)] = nums1[nums1.index(max_num2)], nums2[n - 1]
      operations += 1
    end
  end

  # Check if conditions are satisfied
  if nums1[n - 1] == nums1.max && nums2[n - 1] == nums2.max
    operations
  else
    -1
  end
end
